<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2561] In log4j-core AbstractStringLayout java version detection is not JEP223 compatible</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2561</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The function&#160;isPreJava8() will detect java 9 and higher as being pre java&#160;8, because the logic does not take&#160;JEP223 into account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same logic is correct in&#160;org.apache.logging.log4j.util.Constants#getMajorVersion, so simply modified the logic in&#160;AbstractStringLayout to work the same in the PR.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems like a small change, but it prevents log4j from being JDK 9 and up compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
